    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei salvatoris Iesu Christi. Nos <rs
                            key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">vir gloriosissimus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis" ref="#people/186"
                            >Sicardus</persName>, Dei providencia, Beneventane provincie <rs
                            key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>, per rogum <persName key="#Intercessory"
                            >Adelfrid</persName> dilecti <rs key="#familyOf">parentis</rs> nostri,
                        concedimus in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Churches #Landed_possessions #Slave_labour #Slave"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Beatissimi Vincencii martyris</orgName>,
                        quod situm est in finibus Samnii, iuxta <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturnum</placeName>, ubi vir
                        venerabilis <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1903">Epyphanius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>, orator noster, preesse videtur, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs> et <rs key="#Slave_labour #Slave"
                            >servos et ancillas</rs>, et <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> vocabulo
                        <orgName key="#Churches #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1905">Sancte Dei
                            genitricis et virginis Marie</orgName>, quam habemus in <rs key="#Fines"
                            >finibus</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Fines #Landed_possessions #Churches #Slave #Slave_labour"
                            ref="#estates/1901">Benafro</geogName>, loco qui nominatur <placeName
                                key="#Churches #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#places/2312">Campiniano</placeName>, que fuit
                            <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannis</name></persName> et <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"
                                ><name ref="Radoaldus">Radoaldi</name></persName>, filiis <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Pico">Picconi</name></persName>;
                        et <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Ermelgrimus"
                                >Ermelgrimi</name></persName>, filii <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Ratepertus"
                            >Rapperti</name></persName>; et <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"
                                ><name ref="Stephanus">Stephani</name></persName>, filii <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Paldo">Paldonis</name></persName>;
                        et <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Truppoaldus"
                                >Truppoaldi</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Petrus">Petri</name></persName>,
                        filii <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Andreas"
                            >Andree</name></persName>; et <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name
                                ref="Ragibertus">Ragemberti</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Radoaldus"
                            >Radoaldi</name></persName>, filii <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"
                                ><name ref="Radipertus">Radiperti</name></persName>; et <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Trasmundus"
                            >Trasemundi</name></persName> et <persName key="#Slave_labour #Slave"
                                ><name ref="Leodemundus">Leodemundi</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Leodelgarius"
                            >Leodelgari</name></persName>, filii <persName
                            key="#Slave_labour #Slave"><name ref="Lupinus">Lupini</name></persName>,
                        per hos fines: prima parte fine <rs key="#Rivers">riagine</rs>, que dicitur
                        <placeName key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#places/2309">Ravennola</placeName>, unde
                        per tempus aqua decurrit; secunda parte fine habet fossato et terra uno se
                        tenente iam dicti monasterii; tercia vero parte fine habet riagine unde per
                        tempus aqua decurrit; quarta denique parte fine habet silice; nam et
                        concedimus iam dictas terras in iam dicto monasterio, cum omnes servos et
                        ancillas, et omnes faccultates eorum, cum filiis, filiabus, cum nuribus et
                        nepotibus, et cum omnibus cespitibus, qui fuerunt et pertinuerunt ad
                        superius nominatos homines, qui pro culpe eorum meritis, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Inflow #Inheritance #Confiscation"
                            >ad sacrum nostrum palacium devenerunt</rs>. que nos concedimus et
                        confirmamus in predicto monasterio omnia possidenda in integrum, in ea
                        videlicet racione, ut a modo et deinceps, per hoc nostrum roboratum
                        preceptum, cuncta, ut superius leguntur, habere et possidere valeatis vos
                        iam nominate Epyphani abbas, atque successoribus et rectoribus iam dicti
                        vestri monasterii, ita ut a nullis ex nostris iudicibus, idest comitibus et
                        castaldeis, vel a quibuscumque hominibus non habeatis de predictis terris et
                        de predicta || ecclesia et servis et ancillis aliquam requisicionem vel
                        molestacionem, sed perpetuis temporibus possideatis. Si quis autem, quod nos
                        non credimus, hoc nostrum roboratum preceptum dirrumpere aut contrare
                        presupmserit in pars iam dicti monasterii iam dictas terras et ecclesiam et
                        iam dictos servos et ancillas, sciat se compositurum in parte iam dicti
                        monasterii solidos mille. Quod vero <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">preceptum</rs>, firmitatis, ex
                        iussione tue potestatis, scripsi ego <persName key="#Notary"><name
                                ref="Leodericus">Leodericus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>. <date>Actum <placeName key="#Palatium"
                                ref="#places/110">Benevento</placeName>, in <rs key="#Palatium"
                                >sacro palacio</rs>, quinto anno principatus eius, mense ianuario,
                            XIIIIa. indiccione</date> feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
